#. Tag: title
#: introduction.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:3
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kxstitch; is a program that lets you create cross stitch patterns and "
"charts. Patterns can be created from scratch on a user defined size of grid, "
"which can be enlarged or reduced in size as your pattern progresses. "
"Alternatively you can import images from many graphics formats. When "
"importing images you can restrict the conversion to full stitches or "
"optionally use fractional stitches. You may also use images as backgrounds "
"resizing them to fit in a selected area. These imported images can then be "
"modified using the supplied tools to produce your final design."
msgstr ""
"&kxstitch; je program, ki vam omogoča ustvarjanje vzorcev križnih šivov in "
"shem. Vzorce lahko ustvarite iz nič na uporabniško določeni velikosti mreže, "
"ki jo je mogoče povečati ali zmanjšati, ko vaš vzorec napreduje. Lahko pa "
"uvozite slike iz številnih grafičnih formatov. Pri uvažanju slik lahko "
"omejite pretvorbo na polne šive ali po želji uporabite delne šive. Slike "
"lahko uporabite tudi kot ozadje in jim spremenite velikost, da se prilegajo "
"izbranemu območju. Te uvožene slike lahko nato spremenite s priloženimi "
"orodji, da ustvarite svoj končni dizajn."

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are many tools to aid designing your pattern, from open and filled "
"rectangles and ellipses, filled polygons and lines and backstitching. "
"Additionally cut, copy and paste can be used to duplicate selected areas. "
"Selected areas can also be rotated 90, 180 and 270 degrees anti clockwise, "
"or mirrored horizontally or vertically."
msgstr ""
"Obstaja veliko orodij za pomoč pri oblikovanju vašega vzorca, od odprtih in "
"zapolnjenih pravokotnikov in elips, zapolnjenih poligonov in črt do hrbtnega "
"šivanja. Poleg tega lahko za podvajanje izbranih področij uporabite "
"izrezovanje, kopiranje in lepljenje. Izbrana območja je mogoče tudi zasukati "
"za 90, 180 in 270 stopinj v nasprotni smeri urinega kazalca ali zrcaliti "
"vodoravno ali navpično."

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is also a pattern library that can be used to store small and not so "
"small portions of patterns that can then be reused in other patterns. The "
"patterns in these libraries are stored in a hierarchical list that makes it "
"easy to sort and navigate them to find the ones you want. These pattern "
"libraries can also be used as alphabets by assigning a character to each "
"one. By using the Alphabet tool, each key press is searched for in the "
"current library and if present, the associated library pattern will be "
"inserted in the pattern."
msgstr ""
"Obstaja tudi knjižnica vzorcev, ki jo lahko uporabite za shranjevanje "
"majhnih in manj majhnih delov vzorcev, ki jih je mogoče nato ponovno "
"uporabiti v drugih vzorcih. Vzorci v teh knjižnicah so shranjeni na "
"hierarhičnem seznamu, ki olajša razvrščanje in krmarjenje po njih, da "
"najdete tiste, ki jih želite. Te knjižnice vzorcev lahko uporabite tudi kot "
"abecede, tako da vsaki dodelite znak. Z uporabo orodja Alphabet se vsak "
"pritisk tipke poišče v trenutni knjižnici in, če je prisotna, bo povezan "
"vzorec knjižnice vstavljen v vzorec."

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:26
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please report any bugs or feature requests to the <ulink url=\"http://bugs."
"kde.org\">KDE Bugtracking System</ulink> or the <ulink url=\"http://mail.kde."
"org/mailman/listinfo/kxstitch\">&kxstitch; mailing list</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Prijavite vse hrošče (napake) ali zahteve po funkcijah <ulink url=\"http://"
"bugs.kde.org\">KDE Bugtracking System</ulink> ali <ulink url=\"http://mail."
"kde.org/mailman /listinfo/kxstitch\">&kxstitch; poštni seznam</ulink>"
